         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translations</head>
            <div type="translation" source="#jmr-jbwp-rgg2003" xml:lang="en"><p>(a) Lord of the hosts be (or, you are) with us, our succour, 
            God of Jacob, mighty God, eternal God, be (or, you are) the shield of your servant Theodoros, the deacon</p>
            <p>(b) This good work also came into being in the time of Theodoros, the most holy new bishop, in indiction 3.</p>
            <p>(c) Your witnesses were trusted; that greatly adorns your house</p></div>
            </div>
        
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>For a more precise date see <ref type="inscription">G03900</ref></p>
            <p>(a) line 1, <bibl>LXXX, Psalms 30, 3 and 5; 45.8 ff; 70,3</bibl>; and <bibl>Isaiah 26, 4</bibl>. 
               For some quotations inscribed elsewhere, cf. <bibl>IGLS IV, 301, 525, 1428, 1453, 1687, 1723, 1726, 1743, 1757, 1912</bibl>;
               line 6, Theodoros: probably also in <ref type="inscription">G04200</ref>.
               If the abbreviation in this title is correctly resolved, he must have begun work in this room immediately 
               after his appointment as deacon and finished it soon after his appointment as bishop, see (b) line 7.</p>
               <p>(b) line 7,Clearly Theodoros succeeded the Makarios of <ref type="inscription">G03900</ref> as bishop, but the style of the mosaics 
               sponsored by the two men is indistinguishable so that the third year of an indiction cited by both is probably
               the same year, i.e. C.E. 539.</p>
               <p>(c) line 6, LXX, Psalm 92,5; for other instances of the second half of the quotation in inscriptions see 
                  <bibl>Ch. Diehl, CR 1920, p.216f.</bibl> and <bibl>IGLS II, 414</bibl>.</p>
         </div>
         
